msContents.summary: Complete copy of an Ottoman region manuscript Qur'an.

supportDesc.extent: 352 leaves : 160 x 103 mm, bound to 161 x 120 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil added, upper left recto and upper right verso; catchwords every verso, lower left.

collation.p: Paper, 352. Catchwords on each leaf, lower left verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black and red ink; pointed and vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Polychrome and gold illuminated frontispiece (f. 1v-2r) with text in cloudbands. Polychrome and gold chapter headings. Gold roundels mark verse endings. Border-rules and page-frame ruled in gold. Polychrome and gold marginal medallions.

binding.p: Dark brown leather binding with medallions and gold decoration.

origin.p: Copy completed in Muḥarram 1143 A.H. (1730 CE) by Dirīsh Muḥammad ibn Mūsá (p. 724).
